/-- The original statement used `NormedAddCommGroup R` with `SMulZeroClass R E` and
`IsBoundedSMul R E`, but that is false in general (take `r = 0`: then `r • f = 0` is
always integrable regardless of `f`). The corrected version requires `NormedField R`,
`Module R E`, and `r ≠ 0`, matching `MeasureTheory.integrable_smul_iff`. -/
theorem intervalIntegrable_iff_intervalIntegrable_smul
